# FASTA Sequence Analyser

A Python tool for comprehensive FASTA file analysis.
Computes GC content, finds open reading frames (ORFs), calculates codon usage,
measures sequence complexity, and generates analysis plots.
Works on both nucleotide and protein FASTA files.

---

## Features

- GC content per sequence
- Nucleotide composition (A/T/G/C/N counts)
- Open reading frame (ORF) detection — all 6 reading frames
- Sequence complexity score (linguistic complexity, 2-mer)
- Codon usage table
- Protein mode: amino acid composition + property analysis
- Multi-sequence FASTA support
- Plain-text report + 4-panel plot

---

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/fasta-sequence-analyser.git
cd fasta-sequence-analyser
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## Usage

```bash
# Nucleotide sequences
python fasta_analyser.py -i sequences.fasta -o results/ --type nucleotide

# Protein sequences
python fasta_analyser.py -i proteins.fasta -o results/ --type protein

# Custom minimum ORF length
python fasta_analyser.py -i genome.fasta -o results/ --orf-min 300
```

